28/09/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia and Montenegro -- Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi said on Saturday (27 September) that he would not start talks with the Serbian government without the approval of the assembly in Pristina, adding that he has asked MPs to come up with a common position. UNMIK and the major world powers have approved direct negotiations on technical issues. The talks are expected to start in Vienna in mid-October.
In other news, a witness in the trial of five former Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) members escaped injury in an apparent assassination attempt in Pec on Friday. An explosive device went off under Ramiz Muriqi's car as he was driving. Two witnesses in other trials against KLA members were murdered earlier this year.(AFP, Beta, B92, Hina - 27/09/03, AFP - 26/09/03)
